<HL>
   Canada's June Retail Sales Rose
</HL>
<DATE>
08/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian retail sales rose 0.8% in June from
May, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   In May, retail sales fell 1%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The June gain was the largest monthly increase since
January, when retail sales rose 1.4%. It was partly
attributed to a rise in sales of automobiles and other
vehicles.
   Retail sales fell 1.7% in the second quarter despite the
June rise, Statistics Canada said.
</TEXT>
